WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.275 --> 00:00:12.579
( gate rumbling.
chains rattling )

2
00:00:41.574 --> 00:00:44.210
( horse snorts )

3
00:00:55.588 --> 00:00:59.092
( rumbling. chain rattling )

4
00:01:14.808 --> 00:01:17.644
( horse whickers )

5
00:01:43.203 --> 00:01:46.106
( wind whispering )

6
00:01:55.482 --> 00:01:58.785
- ( nickers )
- EASY. BOY.

7
00:02:55.375 --> 00:02:57.443
( gasps )

8
00:03:00.180 --> 00:03:02.482
( whinnies )

9
00:03:10.857 --> 00:03:13.259
Man:
WHAT DO YOU EXPECT?
THEY'RE SAVAGES.

10
00:03:13.259 --> 00:03:15.361
ONE LOT STEALS A GOAT
FROM ANOTHER LOT.

11
00:03:15.361 --> 00:03:18.531
BEFORE YOU KNOW IT
THEY'RE RIPPING
EACH OTHER TO PIECES.

12
00:03:18.531 --> 00:03:20.700
I'VE NEVER SEEN WILDLINGS
DO A THING LIKE THIS.

13
00:03:20.700 --> 00:03:22.969
I NEVER SEEN
A THING LIKE THIS.
NOT EVER IN MY LIFE.

14
00:03:22.969 --> 00:03:25.572
- ( horse snorts )
- HOW CLOSE DID YOU GET?

15
00:03:25.572 --> 00:03:29.576
- CLOSE AS ANY MAN WOULD.
- WE SHOULD HEAD BACK
TO THE WALL.

16
00:03:31.611 --> 00:03:33.246
DO THE DEAD FRIGHTEN YOU?

17
00:03:33.246 --> 00:03:35.615
OUR ORDERS WERE
TO TRACK THE WILDLINGS.

18
00:03:35.615 --> 00:03:38.518
WE TRACKED THEM.
THEY WON'T TROUBLE US
NO MORE.

19
00:03:38.518 --> 00:03:41.821
YOU DON'T THINK
HE'LL ASK US HOW THEY DIED?

20
00:03:43.456 --> 00:03:45.725
GET BACK ON YOUR HORSE.

21
00:03:45.725 --> 00:03:47.594
( huffs )

22
00:03:47.594 --> 00:03:49.529
( mutters )

23
00:03:49.696 --> 00:03:51.831
WHATEVER DID IT TO THEM
COULD DO IT TO US.

24
00:03:51.831 --> 00:03:53.700
THEY EVEN KILLED
THE CHILDREN.

25
00:03:53.700 --> 00:03:57.503
IT'S A GOOD THING
WE'RE NOT CHILDREN.

26
00:03:58.471 --> 00:04:00.840
YOU WANT TO RUN AWAY SOUTH.
RUN AWAY.

27
00:04:00.840 --> 00:04:04.310
OF COURSE THEY WILL
BEHEAD YOU AS A DESERTER.

28
00:04:04.310 --> 00:04:07.013
IF I DON'T
CATCH YOU FIRST.

29
00:04:08.781 --> 00:04:11.317
GET BACK ON YOUR HORSE.

30
00:04:11.317 --> 00:04:13.519
I WON'T SAY IT AGAIN.

31
00:04:31.404 --> 00:04:33.973
( echoing animal call )

32
00:04:44.517 --> 00:04:47.587
YOUR DEAD MEN SEEM
TO HAVE MOVED CAMP.

33
00:04:47.587 --> 00:04:50.456
THEY WERE HERE.

34
00:04:53.326 --> 00:04:55.895
SEE WHERE THEY WENT.

35
00:05:10.710 --> 00:05:13.413
( echoing calls )

36
00:05:41.374 --> 00:05:43.643
WHAT IS IT?

37
00:05:43.643 --> 00:05:46.112
IT'S...

38
00:05:46.846 --> 00:05:49.082
( crackles )

39
00:05:50.917 --> 00:05:53.353
( distant scream )

40
00:05:53.353 --> 00:05:54.053
( horses neighing )

41
00:05:54.053 --> 00:05:57.690
( hoofbeats )

42
00:06:25.818 --> 00:06:28.821
( crackling. snarling )

43
00:06:28.821 --> 00:06:31.624
( chittering noises )

44
00:06:39.565 --> 00:06:41.734
( coughing )

45
00:06:45.405 --> 00:06:47.507
( panting )

46
00:06:47.507 --> 00:06:49.475
( wheezing )

47
00:06:50.076 --> 00:06:52.412
( hissing breath )

48
00:06:54.680 --> 00:06:57.683
( gasps )

49
00:06:59.952 --> 00:07:03.089
( crackling )

50
00:07:08.094 --> 00:07:11.164
( crackling )

51
00:07:11.164 --> 00:07:13.800
( chittering )

52
00:07:15.735 --> 00:08:23.069
( theme music playing )

53
00:09:00.573 --> 00:09:02.808
( hoofbeats )

54
00:09:42.882 --> 00:09:44.684
( stomps )

55
00:09:48.220 --> 00:09:51.791
GO ON. FATHER'S WATCHING.

56
00:09:53.693 --> 00:09:55.728
AND YOUR MOTHER.

57
00:10:01.167 --> 00:10:04.904
FINE WORK AS ALWAYS.
WELL DONE.

58
00:10:04.904 --> 00:10:05.905
THANK YOU.

59
00:10:05.905 --> 00:10:10.876
I LOVE THE DETAIL THAT
YOU'VE MANAGED TO GET
IN THESE CORNERS.

60
00:10:10.876 --> 00:10:12.845
QUITE BEAUTIFUL.

61
00:10:12.845 --> 00:10:15.047
THE STITCHING...

62
00:10:16.849 --> 00:10:19.719
( arrows thunk. laughter )

63
00:10:33.299 --> 00:10:35.267
- ( sighs )
- ( laughing )

64
00:10:35.267 --> 00:10:38.838
AND WHICH ONE OF YOU
WAS A MARKSMAN AT 10?

65
00:10:39.372 --> 00:10:41.407
KEEP PRACTICING. BRAN.

66
00:10:43.209 --> 00:10:44.844
GO ON.

67
00:10:44.844 --> 00:10:48.247
DON'T THINK
TOO MUCH. BRAN.

68
00:10:50.216 --> 00:10:52.685
RELAX YOUR BOW ARM.

69
00:11:01.661 --> 00:11:03.229
( men laugh )

70
00:11:03.229 --> 00:11:06.232
QUICK. BRAN!
FASTER.

71
00:11:07.800 --> 00:11:10.169
LORD STARK!

72
00:11:10.970 --> 00:11:13.305
MY LADY.

73
00:11:13.305 --> 00:11:15.174
A GUARDSMAN JUST
RODE IN FROM THE HILLS.

74
00:11:15.174 --> 00:11:19.145
THEY'VE CAPTURED A DESERTER
FROM THE NIGHT'S WATCH.

75
00:11:21.747 --> 00:11:24.283
GET THE LADS TO SADDLE
THEIR HORSES.

76
00:11:24.283 --> 00:11:26.252
DO YOU HAVE TO?

77
00:11:26.252 --> 00:11:28.788
HE SWORE AN OATH. CAT.

78
00:11:28.788 --> 00:11:31.223
THE LAW IS LAW.
MY LADY.

79
00:11:31.891 --> 00:11:34.226
TELL BRAN HE'S COMING TOO.

80
00:11:35.895 --> 00:11:37.063
NED.

81
00:11:37.063 --> 00:11:39.398
10 IS TOO YOUNG
TO SEE SUCH THINGS.

82
00:11:39.398 --> 00:11:41.867
HE WON'T BE A BOY FOREVER.

83
00:11:43.436 --> 00:11:46.205
AND WINTER IS COMING.

84
00:12:04.023 --> 00:12:08.260
LAD. GO RUN BACK
AND GET THE REST.

85
00:12:12.298 --> 00:12:14.233
( muttering )
WHITE WALKERS.

86
00:12:14.233 --> 00:12:17.169
I SAW THE WHITE WALKERS.

87
00:12:17.169 --> 00:12:18.871
WHITE WALKERS.

88
00:12:18.871 --> 00:12:22.308
THE WHITE WALKERS.
I SAW THEM.

89
00:12:22.308 --> 00:12:25.845
( pants )

90
00:12:30.883 --> 00:12:33.185
I KNOW I BROKE MY OATH.

91
00:12:33.953 --> 00:12:35.287
AND I KNOW
I'M A DESERTER.

92
00:12:35.287 --> 00:12:39.492
I SHOULD HAVE
GONE BACK TO THE WALL
AND WARNED THEM. BUT--

93
00:12:39.492 --> 00:12:41.794
I SAW WHAT I SAW.

94
00:12:41.794 --> 00:12:44.263
I SAW THE WHITE WALKERS.

95
00:12:45.831 --> 00:12:48.200
PEOPLE NEED TO KNOW.

96
00:12:49.835 --> 00:12:51.537
IF YOU CAN GET WORD
TO MY FAMILY...

97
00:12:51.537 --> 00:12:54.140
TELL THEM I'M NO COWARD.

98
00:12:54.140 --> 00:12:56.475
TELL THEM I'M SORRY.

99
00:13:12.992 --> 00:13:15.361
( whispers )
FORGIVE ME. LORD.

100
00:13:18.397 --> 00:13:21.267
IN THE NAME OF ROBERT
OF THE HOUSE BARATHEON.

101
00:13:21.267 --> 00:13:23.035
- THE FIRST OF HIS NAME...
- DON'T LOOK AWAY.

102
00:13:23.035 --> 00:13:25.538
- ...KING OF THE ANDALS
AND THE FIRST MEN...
- FATHER WILL KNOW IF YOU DO.

103
00:13:25.538 --> 00:13:29.842
...LORD OF THE SEVEN KINGDOMS
AND PROTECTOR OF THE REALM.

104
00:13:29.842 --> 00:13:32.411
I. EDDARD OF THE HOUSE STARK.

105
00:13:32.411 --> 00:13:35.581
LORD OF WINTERFELL
AND WARDEN OF THE NORTH.

106
00:13:35.581 --> 00:13:38.551
SENTENCE YOU TO DIE.

107
00:13:52.865 --> 00:13:55.467
YOU DID WELL.

108
00:14:22.361 --> 00:14:24.363
YOU UNDERSTAND
WHY I DID IT?

109
00:14:24.363 --> 00:14:26.065
JON SAID
HE WAS A DESERTER.

110
00:14:26.065 --> 00:14:28.934
BUT DO YOU UNDERSTAND
WHY I HAD TO KILL HIM?

111
00:14:28.934 --> 00:14:31.203
"OUR WAY IS THE OLD WAY"?

112
00:14:32.238 --> 00:14:34.340
THE MAN WHO PASSES
THE SENTENCE

113
00:14:34.340 --> 00:14:36.342
SHOULD SWING THE SWORD.

114
00:14:36.942 --> 00:14:39.945
IS IT TRUE HE SAW
THE WHITE WALKERS?

115
00:14:40.546 --> 00:14:44.450
THE WHITE WALKERS HAVE BEEN
GONE FOR THOUSANDS OF YEARS.

116
00:14:44.450 --> 00:14:47.386
SO HE WAS LYING?

117
00:14:50.990 --> 00:14:54.360
A MADMAN SEES WHAT HE SEES.

118
00:15:19.685 --> 00:15:22.321
WHAT IS IT?

119
00:15:23.589 --> 00:15:26.592
MOUNTAIN LION?

120
00:15:27.259 --> 00:15:30.062
THERE ARE NO MOUNTAIN LIONS
IN THESE WOODS.

121
00:15:56.956 --> 00:15:59.425
( pup whines )

122
00:16:00.592 --> 00:16:03.495
( yips )

123
00:16:15.607 --> 00:16:18.110
IT'S A FREAK!

124
00:16:18.477 --> 00:16:21.547
IT'S A DIREWOLF.

125
00:16:29.254 --> 00:16:32.324
TOUGH OLD BEAST.

126
00:16:32.658 --> 00:16:36.128
THERE ARE NO DIREWOLVES
SOUTH OF THE WALL.

127
00:16:36.128 --> 00:16:38.263
NOW THERE ARE FIVE.

128
00:16:38.263 --> 00:16:41.333
YOU WANT TO HOLD IT?

129
00:16:43.002 --> 00:16:45.004
( pup whimpers )

130
00:16:45.004 --> 00:16:47.606
Bran:
WHERE WILL THEY GO?

131
00:16:47.606 --> 00:16:49.341
THEIR MOTHER'S DEAD.

132
00:16:49.341 --> 00:16:51.143
THEY DON'T BELONG
DOWN HERE.

133
00:16:51.143 --> 00:16:52.611
BETTER
A QUICK DEATH.

134
00:16:52.611 --> 00:16:54.747
THEY WON'T LAST
WITHOUT THEIR
MOTHER.

135
00:16:54.747 --> 00:16:57.016
- RIGHT. GIVE IT HERE.
- NO!

136
00:16:57.016 --> 00:16:58.517
- ( whimpers )
- PUT AWAY YOUR BLADE.

137
00:16:58.517 --> 00:17:01.020
I TAKE ORDERS
FROM YOUR FATHER.
NOT YOU.

138
00:17:01.020 --> 00:17:04.223
- PLEASE. FATHER!
- I'M SORRY. BRAN.

139
00:17:04.223 --> 00:17:05.791
LORD STARK?

140
00:17:05.791 --> 00:17:08.727
THERE ARE
FIVE PUPS...

141
00:17:09.495 --> 00:17:11.063
ONE FOR EACH
OF THE STARK CHILDREN.

142
00:17:11.063 --> 00:17:14.633
- ( pup cries )
- THE DIREWOLF IS
THE SIGIL OF YOUR HOUSE.

143
00:17:15.434 --> 00:17:18.203
THEY WERE MEANT
TO HAVE THEM.

144
00:17:23.108 --> 00:17:25.611
YOU WILL TRAIN THEM
YOURSELVES.

145
00:17:25.611 --> 00:17:27.346
YOU WILL
FEED THEM YOURSELVES.

146
00:17:27.346 --> 00:17:31.216
AND IF THEY DIE.
YOU WILL BURY THEM
YOURSELVES.

147
00:17:39.091 --> 00:17:41.560
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

148
00:17:41.794 --> 00:17:43.662
I'M NOT A STARK.

149
00:17:43.662 --> 00:17:46.265
GET ON.

150
00:17:52.704 --> 00:17:55.074
( whimpers )

151
00:17:55.074 --> 00:17:57.576
WHAT IS IT?

152
00:18:00.679 --> 00:18:05.584
THE RUNT OF THE LITTER--
THAT ONE'S YOURS. SNOW.

153
00:18:13.659 --> 00:18:17.129
( bells tolling )

154
00:19:04.343 --> 00:19:08.447
AS YOUR BROTHER.
I FEEL IT'S MY DUTY
TO WARN YOU:

155
00:19:09.515 --> 00:19:10.682
YOU WORRY TOO MUCH.

156
00:19:10.682 --> 00:19:15.354
- IT'S STARTING TO SHOW.
- AND YOU NEVER WORRY
ABOUT ANYTHING.

157
00:19:15.687 --> 00:19:19.892
WHEN WE WERE SEVEN
AND YOU JUMPED OFF
THE CLIFFS AT CASTERLY ROCK.

158
00:19:19.892 --> 00:19:22.528
100-FOOT DROP INTO THE WATER.

159
00:19:22.528 --> 00:19:23.929
AND YOU WERE NEVER AFRAID.

160
00:19:23.929 --> 00:19:26.798
THERE WAS NOTHING
TO BE AFRAID OF
UNTIL YOU TOLD FATHER.

161
00:19:26.798 --> 00:19:28.867
( whispers. mimicking )
"WE'RE LANNISTERS.

162
00:19:28.867 --> 00:19:31.937
LANNISTERS
DON'T ACT LIKE FOOLS."

163
00:19:33.205 --> 00:19:35.641
WHAT IF JON ARRYN
TOLD SOMEONE?

164
00:19:35.641 --> 00:19:37.709
BUT WHO WOULD HE TELL?

165
00:19:37.709 --> 00:19:40.779
- MY HUSBAND.
- IF HE TOLD THE KING.
BOTH OUR HEADS

166
00:19:40.779 --> 00:19:43.815
WOULD BE SKEWERED
ON THE CITY GATES BY NOW.

167
00:19:44.516 --> 00:19:47.352
WHATEVER JON ARRYN
KNEW OR DIDN'T KNOW.
IT DIED WITH HIM.

168
00:19:47.352 --> 00:19:51.523
AND ROBERT WILL CHOOSE
A NEW HAND OF THE KING--
SOMEONE TO DO HIS JOB

169
00:19:51.523 --> 00:19:54.760
WHILE HE'S OFF FUCKING BOARS
AND HUNTING WHORES--

170
00:19:54.760 --> 00:19:57.729
OR IS IT
THE OTHER WAY AROUND?

171
00:19:57.729 --> 00:19:59.831
AND LIFE WILL GO ON.

172
00:19:59.831 --> 00:20:02.668
YOU SHOULD BE
THE HAND OF THE KING.

173
00:20:02.668 --> 00:20:05.504
THAT'S AN HONOR
I CAN DO WITHOUT.

174
00:20:05.504 --> 00:20:07.639
THEIR DAYS ARE TOO LONG.

175
00:20:07.639 --> 00:20:10.409
THEIR LIVES ARE TOO SHORT.

176
00:20:13.712 --> 00:20:16.782
( thunder rumbles )

177
00:20:21.787 --> 00:20:23.522
( caws )

178
00:20:37.336 --> 00:20:40.372
( birds chirping )

179
00:20:48.547 --> 00:20:49.781
ALL THESE YEARS

180
00:20:49.781 --> 00:20:51.717
AND I STILL FEEL
LIKE AN OUTSIDER

181
00:20:51.717 --> 00:20:53.752
WHEN I COME HERE.

182
00:20:53.752 --> 00:20:56.622
YOU HAVE FIVE
NORTHERN CHILDREN.

183
00:20:56.622 --> 00:20:59.591
YOU'RE NOT AN OUTSIDER.

184
00:20:59.591 --> 00:21:03.362
I WONDER
IF THE OLD GODS AGREE.

185
00:21:03.695 --> 00:21:07.466
IT'S YOUR GODS
WITH ALL THE RULES.

186
00:21:11.903 --> 00:21:15.507
I AM SO SORRY. MY LOVE.

187
00:21:15.807 --> 00:21:20.445
- TELL ME.
- THERE WAS A RAVEN
FROM KING'S LANDING.

188
00:21:21.747 --> 00:21:23.582
JON ARRYN IS DEAD.

189
00:21:23.582 --> 00:21:26.451
A FEVER TOOK HIM.

190
00:21:28.520 --> 00:21:31.490
I KNOW HE WAS LIKE
A FATHER TO YOU.

191
00:21:33.492 --> 00:21:37.529
- YOUR SISTER. THE BOY?
- THEY BOTH HAVE THEIR HEALTH.

192
00:21:37.529 --> 00:21:39.831
GODS BE GOOD.

193
00:21:48.974 --> 00:21:52.444
THE RAVEN
BROUGHT MORE NEWS...

194
00:21:53.078 --> 00:21:55.514
THE KING RIDES
FOR WINTERFELL...

195
00:21:55.514 --> 00:21:57.082
WITH THE QUEEN

196
00:21:57.082 --> 00:21:59.318
AND ALL THE REST
OF THEM.

197
00:21:59.318 --> 00:22:03.055
IF HE'S COMING
THIS FAR NORTH...

198
00:22:03.789 --> 00:22:06.058
THERE'S ONLY
ONE THING HE'S AFTER.

199
00:22:06.058 --> 00:22:09.628
YOU CAN ALWAYS SAY NO. NED.

200
00:22:17.436 --> 00:22:21.573
Catelyn:
WE'LL NEED PLENTY OF CANDLES
FOR LORD TYRION'S CHAMBER.

201
00:22:21.573 --> 00:22:23.742
I'M TOLD HE READS
ALL NIGHT.

202
00:22:23.742 --> 00:22:25.344
I'M TOLD HE DRINKS
ALL NIGHT.

203
00:22:25.344 --> 00:22:29.348
HOW MUCH COULD
HE POSSIBLY DRINK?
A MAN OF HIS...

204
00:22:29.348 --> 00:22:30.415
STATURE?

205
00:22:30.415 --> 00:22:33.118
WE'VE BROUGHT UP
EIGHT BARRELS OF ALE
FROM THE CELLAR.

206
00:22:33.118 --> 00:22:36.421
- PERHAPS WE'LL FIND OUT.
- IN ANY CASE.

207
00:22:36.421 --> 00:22:39.091
CANDLES.

208
00:22:42.060 --> 00:22:45.464
WHY IS YOUR MOTHER
SO DEAD SET ON US GETTING
PRETTY FOR THE KING?

209
00:22:45.464 --> 00:22:48.467
IT'S FOR THE QUEEN. I BET.
I HEAR SHE'S A SLEEK
BIT OF MINK.

210
00:22:48.467 --> 00:22:50.402
I HEAR THE PRINCE
IS A RIGHT ROYAL PRICK.

211
00:22:50.402 --> 00:22:52.637
THINK OF ALL THOSE
SOUTHERN GIRLS
HE GETS TO STAB

212
00:22:52.637 --> 00:22:54.740
WITH HIS RIGHT
ROYAL PRICK.

213
00:22:56.074 --> 00:22:57.843
GO ON. TOMMY.
SHEAR HIM GOOD.

214
00:22:57.843 --> 00:23:01.146
HE'S NEVER MET
A GIRL HE LIKES BETTER
THAN HIS OWN HAIR.

215
00:23:01.146 --> 00:23:03.548
( laughter )

216
00:23:37.649 --> 00:23:41.153
- ( pup barks )
- GODS. BUT THEY GROW FAST.

217
00:23:43.522 --> 00:23:44.122
BRANDON!

218
00:23:44.122 --> 00:23:47.526
I SAW THE KING.
HE'S GOT HUNDREDS
OF PEOPLE.

219
00:23:47.526 --> 00:23:50.796
HOW MANY TIMES
HAVE I TOLD YOU
NO CLIMBING?

220
00:23:50.796 --> 00:23:54.433
BUT HE'S
COMING RIGHT NOW--
DOWN OUR ROAD.

221
00:24:00.839 --> 00:24:03.542
I WANT YOU
TO PROMISE ME.

222
00:24:03.542 --> 00:24:05.710
NO MORE CLIMBING.

223
00:24:09.848 --> 00:24:11.716
I PROMISE.

224
00:24:13.618 --> 00:24:16.087
- DO YOU KNOW WHAT?
- WHAT?

225
00:24:16.087 --> 00:24:19.090
YOU ALWAYS LOOK
AT YOUR FEET BEFORE YOU LIE.

226
00:24:19.090 --> 00:24:20.926
( chuckles )

227
00:24:20.926 --> 00:24:25.497
RUN AND FIND YOUR FATHER.
TELL HIM THE KING IS CLOSE.

228
00:25:08.673 --> 00:25:13.144
WHERE'S ARYA?
SANSA. WHERE'S YOUR SISTER?

229
00:25:22.787 --> 00:25:24.523
- HEY HEY HEY HEY.
- OHH.

230
00:25:24.523 --> 00:25:27.225
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
WITH THAT ON?

231
00:25:29.528 --> 00:25:32.197
- GO ON.
- ( Arya groans )

232
00:25:33.298 --> 00:25:35.300
MOVE!

233
00:25:52.584 --> 00:25:54.986
( neighs )

234
00:26:57.082 --> 00:26:59.351
YOUR GRACE.

235
00:27:03.088 --> 00:27:05.357
YOU'VE GOT FAT.

236
00:27:11.796 --> 00:27:14.265
( laughter )

237
00:27:17.202 --> 00:27:20.271
- CAT!
- YOUR GRACE.

238
00:27:22.273 --> 00:27:25.844
NINE YEARS--
WHY HAVEN'T I SEEN YOU?
WHERE THE HELL HAVE YOU BEEN?

239
00:27:25.844 --> 00:27:28.013
GUARDING THE NORTH
FOR YOU. YOUR GRACE.

240
00:27:28.013 --> 00:27:31.216
WINTERFELL IS YOURS.

241
00:27:33.718 --> 00:27:36.187
- WHERE'S THE IMP?
- WILL YOU SHUT UP?

242
00:27:36.187 --> 00:27:39.057
Robert:
WHO HAVE WE HERE?

243
00:27:39.057 --> 00:27:41.192
YOU MUST BE ROBB.

244
00:27:43.395 --> 00:27:47.198
MY. YOU'RE
A PRETTY ONE.

245
00:27:47.198 --> 00:27:49.334
YOUR NAME IS?

246
00:27:49.334 --> 00:27:51.403
ARYA.

247
00:27:51.403 --> 00:27:55.140
OH. SHOW US
YOUR MUSCLES.

248
00:27:56.708 --> 00:27:58.243
YOU'LL BE A SOLDIER.

249
00:28:00.011 --> 00:28:03.314
Arya:
THAT'S JAIME LANNISTER.
THE QUEEN'S TWIN BROTHER.

250
00:28:03.314 --> 00:28:06.117
Sansa:
WOULD YOU PLEASE SHUT UP?

251
00:28:15.326 --> 00:28:18.396
MY QUEEN.

252
00:28:18.396 --> 00:28:20.965
TAKE ME TO YOUR CRYPT.
I WANT TO PAY MY RESPECTS.

253
00:28:20.965 --> 00:28:23.468
WE'VE BEEN RIDING
FOR A MONTH. MY LOVE.

254
00:28:23.468 --> 00:28:25.737
SURELY THE DEAD CAN WAIT.

255
00:28:25.737 --> 00:28:27.872
NED.

256
00:28:36.881 --> 00:28:38.817
WHERE'S THE IMP?

257
00:28:41.486 --> 00:28:43.822
WHERE IS OUR BROTHER?

258
00:28:43.822 --> 00:28:46.391
GO AND FIND
THE LITTLE BEAST.

259
00:28:48.026 --> 00:28:50.328
TELL ME ABOUT
JON ARRYN.

260
00:28:50.328 --> 00:28:53.398
ONE MINUTE
HE WAS FINE AND THEN...

261
00:28:54.065 --> 00:28:57.769
BURNED RIGHT THROUGH HIM.
WHATEVER IT WAS.

262
00:28:58.403 --> 00:29:00.472
I LOVED THAT MAN.

263
00:29:00.472 --> 00:29:01.306
WE BOTH DID.

264
00:29:01.306 --> 00:29:05.009
Robert:
HE NEVER HAD TO TEACH
YOU MUCH. BUT ME?

265
00:29:05.009 --> 00:29:06.077
YOU REMEMBER ME AT 16?

266
00:29:06.077 --> 00:29:08.079
- ( chuckles )
- ALL I WANTED TO DO

267
00:29:08.079 --> 00:29:10.882
WAS CRACK SKULLS
AND FUCK GIRLS.

268
00:29:10.882 --> 00:29:13.184
- HE SHOWED ME WHAT WAS WHAT.
- AYE.

269
00:29:13.184 --> 00:29:17.455
DON'T LOOK AT ME LIKE THAT.
IT'S NOT HIS FAULT
I DIDN'T LISTEN.

270
00:29:21.192 --> 00:29:22.861
I NEED YOU. NED--

271
00:29:22.861 --> 00:29:27.832
DOWN AT KING'S LANDING.
NOT UP HERE WHERE YOU'RE
NO DAMN USE TO ANYBODY.

272
00:29:29.000 --> 00:29:31.770
LORD EDDARD STARK.

273
00:29:31.770 --> 00:29:34.873
I WOULD NAME YOU
THE HAND OF THE KING.

274
00:29:38.977 --> 00:29:40.211
I'M NOT WORTHY
OF THE HONOR.

275
00:29:40.211 --> 00:29:44.215
I'M NOT TRYING TO HONOR YOU.
I'M TRYING TO GET YOU
TO RUN MY KINGDOM

276
00:29:44.215 --> 00:29:48.286
WHILE I EAT. DRINK AND WHORE
MY WAY TO AN EARLY GRAVE.

277
00:29:48.286 --> 00:29:50.855
DAMN IT. NED. STAND UP.

278
00:29:51.489 --> 00:29:53.925
YOU HELPED ME WIN
THE IRON THRONE.

279
00:29:53.925 --> 00:29:56.461
NOW HELP ME
KEEP THE DAMN THING.

280
00:29:56.861 --> 00:29:58.496
WE WERE MEANT
TO RULE TOGETHER.

281
00:29:58.496 --> 00:30:03.134
IF YOUR SISTER HAD LIVED.
WE'D HAVE BEEN BOUND BY BLOOD.

282
00:30:03.134 --> 00:30:06.004
WELL. IT'S NOT TOO LATE.

283
00:30:06.938 --> 00:30:09.340
I HAVE A SON.
YOU HAVE A DAUGHTER.

284
00:30:10.809 --> 00:30:12.844
WE'LL JOIN OUR HOUSES.

285
00:30:16.881 --> 00:30:19.818
( woman moaning )

286
00:30:28.526 --> 00:30:31.896
( moaning )

287
00:30:35.600 --> 00:30:40.605
- ( cup falls )
- IT IS TRUE WHAT THEY SAY
ABOUT THE NORTHERN GIRLS.

288
00:30:40.605 --> 00:30:43.441
( giggles )

289
00:30:48.413 --> 00:30:50.949
DID YOU HEAR THE KING'S
IN WINTERFELL?

290
00:30:50.949 --> 00:30:52.851
I DID HEAR
SOMETHING ABOUT THAT.

291
00:30:52.851 --> 00:30:54.519
AND THE QUEEN
AND HER TWIN BROTHER.

292
00:30:54.519 --> 00:30:58.356
THEY SAY THAT HE IS
THE MOST HANDSOME MAN
IN THE SEVEN KINGDOMS.

293
00:30:58.356 --> 00:30:59.958
AND THE OTHER BROTHER?

294
00:30:59.958 --> 00:31:03.561
- THE QUEEN HAS TWO BROTHERS?
- THERE'S THE PRETTY ONE.

295
00:31:03.561 --> 00:31:07.098
AND THERE'S
THE CLEVER ONE.

296
00:31:08.333 --> 00:31:11.469
MMM. I HEAR THEY
CALL HIM THE IMP.

297
00:31:11.469 --> 00:31:13.471
I HEAR HE HATES
THAT NICKNAME.

298
00:31:13.471 --> 00:31:16.941
OH?
I HEAR HE'S
MORE THAN EARNED IT.

299
00:31:16.941 --> 00:31:19.544
I HEAR HE'S A DRUNKEN
LITTLE LECHER.

300
00:31:19.544 --> 00:31:22.413
PRONE TO ALL MANNER
OF PERVERSIONS.

301
00:31:22.413 --> 00:31:24.616
CLEVER GIRL.

302
00:31:25.350 --> 00:31:28.219
WE'VE BEEN EXPECTING YOU.
LORD TYRION.

303
00:31:29.287 --> 00:31:31.122
HAVE YOU?

304
00:31:31.122 --> 00:31:33.358
- OH!
- ALREADY?

305
00:31:34.959 --> 00:31:37.629
THE GODS GAVE ME
ONE BLESSING.

306
00:31:37.629 --> 00:31:40.064
( door opens )

307
00:31:42.400 --> 00:31:44.602
- DON'T GET UP.
- MY LORD.

308
00:31:44.602 --> 00:31:46.905
SHOULD I EXPLAIN TO YOU
THE MEANING OF A CLOSED DOOR

309
00:31:46.905 --> 00:31:50.942
- IN A WHOREHOUSE. BROTHER?
- YOU HAVE MUCH TO TEACH ME.
NO DOUBT.

310
00:31:50.942 --> 00:31:54.679
BUT OUR SISTER CRAVES
YOUR ATTENTION.

311
00:31:54.679 --> 00:31:57.048
SHE HAS ODD CRAVINGS.
OUR SISTER.

312
00:31:57.048 --> 00:31:58.583
A FAMILY TRAIT.

313
00:31:58.583 --> 00:32:01.619
NOW THE STARKS ARE
FEASTING US AT SUNDOWN.

314
00:32:01.619 --> 00:32:03.955
DON'T LEAVE ME ALONE
WITH THESE PEOPLE.

315
00:32:03.955 --> 00:32:06.457
I'M SORRY. I'VE BEGUN
THE FEAST A BIT EARLY.

316
00:32:06.457 --> 00:32:09.694
AND THIS IS THE FIRST
OF MANY COURSES.

317
00:32:09.694 --> 00:32:12.096
I THOUGHT
YOU MIGHT SAY THAT.

318
00:32:12.096 --> 00:32:14.599
BUT SINCE
WE'RE SHORT ON TIME...

319
00:32:14.599 --> 00:32:16.601
COME ON. GIRLS.

320
00:32:16.601 --> 00:32:19.570
( giggling )

321
00:32:21.606 --> 00:32:24.075
SEE YOU AT SUNDOWN.

322
00:32:24.075 --> 00:32:27.145
Tyrion:
CLOSE THE DOOR!

323
00:32:38.423 --> 00:32:42.260
DID YOU HAVE TO BURY HER
IN A PLACE LIKE THIS?

324
00:32:43.361 --> 00:32:45.630
SHE SHOULD BE
ON A HILL SOMEWHERE

325
00:32:45.630 --> 00:32:48.599
WITH THE SUN
AND THE CLOUDS ABOVE HER.

326
00:32:48.599 --> 00:32:50.468
SHE WAS MY SISTER.

327
00:32:50.468 --> 00:32:53.338
THIS IS WHERE
SHE BELONGS.

328
00:32:53.338 --> 00:32:56.307
SHE BELONGED WITH ME.

329
00:33:01.045 --> 00:33:05.049
IN MY DREAMS.
I KILL HIM EVERY NIGHT.

330
00:33:06.117 --> 00:33:08.586
IT'S DONE. YOUR GRACE.

331
00:33:08.586 --> 00:33:11.489
THE TARGARYENS ARE GONE.

332
00:33:13.358 --> 00:33:15.994
NOT ALL OF THEM.

333
00:33:17.161 --> 00:33:19.430
( gull cawing )

334
00:33:26.471 --> 00:33:28.673
Man:
DAENERYS!

335
00:33:31.542 --> 00:33:33.211
DAENERYS.

336
00:33:33.211 --> 00:33:35.513
THERE'S OUR BRIDE-TO-BE.

337
00:33:36.114 --> 00:33:39.550
LOOK. A GIFT
FROM ILLYRIO.

338
00:33:40.585 --> 00:33:42.186
TOUCH IT.

339
00:33:42.186 --> 00:33:44.622
GO ON.
FEEL THE FABRIC.

340
00:33:49.327 --> 00:33:51.429
MMM.

341
00:33:52.296 --> 00:33:55.433
ISN'T HE A GRACIOUS HOST?

342
00:33:57.068 --> 00:33:59.170
WE'VE BEEN HIS GUESTS
FOR OVER A YEAR

343
00:33:59.170 --> 00:34:01.472
AND HE'S NEVER
ASKED US FOR ANYTHING.

344
00:34:01.472 --> 00:34:02.774
ILLYRIO'S NO FOOL.

345
00:34:02.774 --> 00:34:05.443
HE KNOWS I WON'T
FORGET MY FRIENDS

346
00:34:05.443 --> 00:34:08.046
WHEN I COME
INTO MY THRONE.

347
00:34:11.582 --> 00:34:14.619
YOU STILL SLOUCH.

348
00:34:18.189 --> 00:34:20.725
LET THEM SEE.

349
00:34:22.760 --> 00:34:26.397
YOU HAVE
A WOMAN'S BODY NOW.

350
00:34:29.133 --> 00:34:31.202
( sighs )

351
00:34:43.514 --> 00:34:46.851
I NEED YOU TO BE
PERFECT TODAY.

352
00:34:47.785 --> 00:34:50.388
CAN YOU DO THAT FOR ME?

353
00:34:52.657 --> 00:34:56.360
YOU DON'T WANT TO WAKE
THE DRAGON. DO YOU?

354
00:34:57.628 --> 00:34:59.363
NO.

355
00:35:05.403 --> 00:35:08.706
WHEN THEY WRITE THE HISTORY
OF MY REIGN. SWEET SISTER.

356
00:35:08.706 --> 00:35:11.509
THEY WILL SAY
IT BEGAN TODAY.

357
00:35:34.198 --> 00:35:37.135
IT'S TOO HOT. MY LADY.

358
00:35:47.245 --> 00:35:49.814
( gulls cawing )

359
00:35:57.488 --> 00:35:59.223
WHERE IS HE?

360
00:35:59.223 --> 00:36:02.593
THE DOTHRAKI
ARE NOT KNOWN
FOR THEIR PUNCTUALITY.

361
00:36:14.672 --> 00:36:19.610
( Illyrio speaking Dothraki )
ATHCHOMAR CHOMAKAAN.
KHAL VEZHVEN.

362
00:36:19.610 --> 00:36:21.646
MAY I PRESENT
MY HONORED GUESTS?

363
00:36:21.646 --> 00:36:25.383
VISERYS
OF HOUSE TARGARYEN.

364
00:36:25.383 --> 00:36:26.651
THE THIRD OF HIS NAME.

365
00:36:26.651 --> 00:36:30.621
THE RIGHTFUL KING OF THE ANDALS
AND THE FIRST MEN.

366
00:36:30.621 --> 00:36:31.956
AND HIS SISTER

367
00:36:31.956 --> 00:36:35.359
DAENERYS
OF HOUSE TARGARYEN.

368
00:36:35.693 --> 00:36:37.562
( speaking Dothraki )

369
00:36:37.562 --> 00:36:39.864
DO YOU SEE
HOW LONG HIS HAIR IS?

370
00:36:39.864 --> 00:36:42.366
WHEN DOTHRAKI ARE
DEFEATED IN COMBAT.

371
00:36:42.366 --> 00:36:46.637
THEY CUT OFF THEIR BRAIDS
SO THE WHOLE WORLD CAN
SEE THEIR SHAME.

372
00:36:46.637 --> 00:36:51.442
KHAL DROGO HAS
NEVER BEEN DEFEATED.

373
00:36:51.943 --> 00:36:53.678
HE'S A SAVAGE. OF COURSE.

374
00:36:53.678 --> 00:36:56.681
BUT ONE OF THE FINEST
KILLERS ALIVE.

375
00:36:57.548 --> 00:36:59.717
AND YOU WILL BE HIS QUEEN.

376
00:36:59.717 --> 00:37:02.853
COME FORWARD. MY DEAR.

377
00:37:42.526 --> 00:37:43.661
WHERE IS HE GOING?!

378
00:37:43.661 --> 00:37:46.430
- THE CEREMONY IS OVER.
- BUT HE DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING.

379
00:37:46.430 --> 00:37:48.866
- DID HE LIKE HER?
- TRUST ME. YOUR GRACE.

380
00:37:48.866 --> 00:37:51.969
IF HE DIDN'T LIKE HER.
WE'D KNOW.

381
00:37:54.538 --> 00:37:56.741
IT WON'T BE
LONG NOW.

382
00:37:56.741 --> 00:37:58.643
SOON YOU WILL CROSS
THE NARROW SEA

383
00:37:58.643 --> 00:38:01.479
AND TAKE BACK
YOUR FATHER'S THRONE.

384
00:38:01.479 --> 00:38:04.649
THE PEOPLE
DRINK SECRET TOASTS

385
00:38:04.649 --> 00:38:05.916
TO YOUR HEALTH.

386
00:38:05.916 --> 00:38:08.853
THEY CRY OUT
FOR THEIR TRUE KING.

387
00:38:11.956 --> 00:38:13.758
WHEN WILL THEY
BE MARRIED?

388
00:38:13.758 --> 00:38:17.428
SOON.
THE DOTHRAKI NEVER
STAY STILL FOR LONG.

389
00:38:17.428 --> 00:38:19.997
IS IT TRUE THEY LIE
WITH THEIR HORSES?

390
00:38:19.997 --> 00:38:23.301
I WOULDN'T ASK
KHAL DROGO.

391
00:38:23.301 --> 00:38:25.069
DO YOU TAKE ME
FOR A FOOL?

392
00:38:25.069 --> 00:38:26.704
I TAKE YOU
FOR A KING.

393
00:38:26.704 --> 00:38:29.940
KINGS LACK THE CAUTION
OF COMMON MEN.

394
00:38:29.940 --> 00:38:32.543
MY APOLOGIES IF
I'VE GIVEN OFFENSE.

395
00:38:32.543 --> 00:38:34.645
I KNOW HOW TO PLAY
A MAN LIKE DROGO.

396
00:38:34.645 --> 00:38:37.815
I GIVE HIM A QUEEN
AND HE GIVES ME AN ARMY.

397
00:38:37.815 --> 00:38:41.419
I DON'T WANT
TO BE HIS QUEEN.

398
00:38:45.423 --> 00:38:47.692
I WANT TO GO HOME.

399
00:38:48.592 --> 00:38:49.794
SO DO I.

400
00:38:49.794 --> 00:38:52.763
I WANT US BOTH
TO GO HOME.

401
00:38:52.763 --> 00:38:55.099
BUT THEY TOOK IT FROM US.

402
00:38:55.099 --> 00:38:57.034
SO TELL ME. SWEET SISTER.

403
00:38:57.034 --> 00:38:59.603
HOW DO WE GO HOME?

404
00:39:01.405 --> 00:39:02.606
I DON'T KNOW.

405
00:39:02.606 --> 00:39:06.077
WE GO HOME WITH AN ARMY.

406
00:39:07.445 --> 00:39:10.448
WITH KHAL DROGO'S ARMY.

407
00:39:10.448 --> 00:39:13.551
I WOULD LET
HIS WHOLE TRIBE FUCK YOU--

408
00:39:13.551 --> 00:39:16.754
ALL 40.000 MEN
AND THEIR HORSES TOO

409
00:39:16.754 --> 00:39:19.090
IF THAT'S WHAT IT TOOK.

410
00:39:25.529 --> 00:39:27.798
( kisses )

411
00:39:35.773 --> 00:39:38.142
DO YOU THINK JOFFREY
WILL LIKE ME?

412
00:39:38.142 --> 00:39:40.611
WHAT IF HE THINKS
I'M UGLY?

413
00:39:40.611 --> 00:39:44.915
THEN HE IS
THE STUPIDEST PRINCE
THAT EVER LIVED.

414
00:39:46.884 --> 00:39:48.886
HE'S SO HANDSOME.

415
00:39:48.886 --> 00:39:51.689
WHEN WOULD WE BE MARRIED?
SOON? OR DO WE HAVE TO WAIT?

416
00:39:51.689 --> 00:39:55.426
HUSH NOW.
YOUR FATHER
HASN'T EVEN SAID YES.

417
00:39:55.426 --> 00:39:56.761
WHY WOULD HE SAY NO?

418
00:39:56.761 --> 00:40:00.531
HE'D BE THE SECOND
MOST POWERFUL MAN
IN THE KINGDOMS.

419
00:40:00.531 --> 00:40:02.967
HE'D HAVE TO LEAVE HOME.

420
00:40:02.967 --> 00:40:06.036
HE'D HAVE TO LEAVE ME.

421
00:40:06.036 --> 00:40:08.839
AND SO WOULD YOU.

422
00:40:08.839 --> 00:40:11.575
YOU LEFT YOUR HOME
TO COME HERE.

423
00:40:11.575 --> 00:40:14.912
AND I'D BE QUEEN SOMEDAY.

424
00:40:15.446 --> 00:40:16.847
PLEASE MAKE FATHER
SAY YES!

425
00:40:16.847 --> 00:40:18.616
- SANSA--
- PLEASE PLEASE!

426
00:40:18.616 --> 00:40:22.186
IT'S THE ONLY THING
I EVER WANTED.

427
00:40:25.523 --> 00:40:28.793
( music playing.
people chattering )

428
00:40:32.530 --> 00:40:34.532
( laughter )

429
00:40:35.566 --> 00:40:38.202
FILL THAT UP!
BOYS. RODRIK. COME ON.

430
00:40:38.202 --> 00:40:40.704
COME ON!

431
00:40:58.856 --> 00:41:02.026
IS HE DEAD YET?

432
00:41:05.696 --> 00:41:08.065
UNCLE BENJEN.

433
00:41:08.065 --> 00:41:09.767
( laughs )

434
00:41:09.767 --> 00:41:11.669
YOU GOT BIGGER.

435
00:41:11.669 --> 00:41:16.006
RODE ALL DAY.
DIDN'T WANT TO LEAVE YOU
ALONE WITH THE LANNISTERS.

436
00:41:16.006 --> 00:41:17.808
WHY AREN'T YOU
AT THE FEAST?

437
00:41:17.808 --> 00:41:20.945
LADY STARK THOUGHT
IT MIGHT INSULT
THE ROYAL FAMILY

438
00:41:20.945 --> 00:41:23.080
TO SEAT A BASTARD
IN THEIR MIDST.

439
00:41:23.080 --> 00:41:25.783
WELL. YOU'RE ALWAYS
WELCOME ON THE WALL.

440
00:41:25.783 --> 00:41:28.085
NO BASTARD WAS EVER
REFUSED A SEAT THERE.

441
00:41:28.085 --> 00:41:29.920
SO TAKE ME WITH YOU
WHEN YOU GO BACK.

442
00:41:29.920 --> 00:41:33.090
- JON--
- FATHER WILL LET ME
IF YOU ASK HIM.

443
00:41:33.090 --> 00:41:35.659
I KNOW HE WILL.

444
00:41:37.728 --> 00:41:40.130
THE WALL ISN'T
GOING ANYWHERE.

445
00:41:40.130 --> 00:41:41.532
I'M READY

446
00:41:41.532 --> 00:41:42.500
TO SWEAR YOUR OATH.

447
00:41:42.500 --> 00:41:45.636
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHAT YOU'D BE GIVING UP.

448
00:41:45.636 --> 00:41:47.238
WE HAVE NO FAMILIES.

449
00:41:47.238 --> 00:41:51.675
- NONE OF US
WILL EVER FATHER SONS--
- I DON'T CARE ABOUT THAT!

450
00:41:52.209 --> 00:41:55.579
YOU MIGHT. IF YOU KNEW
WHAT IT MEANT.

451
00:41:56.914 --> 00:41:58.215
( rattles )

452
00:41:58.215 --> 00:42:00.284
I'D BETTER GET INSIDE.

453
00:42:00.284 --> 00:42:03.654
RESCUE YOUR FATHER
FROM HIS GUESTS.

454
00:42:06.257 --> 00:42:08.726
WE'LL TALK LATER.

455
00:42:15.966 --> 00:42:19.537
Tyrion:
YOUR UNCLE'S IN
THE NIGHT'S WATCH.

456
00:42:21.739 --> 00:42:23.941
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
BACK THERE?

457
00:42:23.941 --> 00:42:27.845
PREPARING FOR A NIGHT
WITH YOUR FAMILY.

458
00:42:31.882 --> 00:42:33.984
I'VE ALWAYS WANTED
TO SEE THE WALL.

459
00:42:33.984 --> 00:42:35.719
YOU'RE TYRION LANNISTER.

460
00:42:35.719 --> 00:42:37.121
THE QUEEN'S BROTHER?

461
00:42:37.121 --> 00:42:39.023
MY GREATEST
ACCOMPLISHMENT.

462
00:42:39.023 --> 00:42:43.661
AND YOU--
YOU'RE NED STARK'S
BASTARD. AREN'T YOU?

463
00:42:46.597 --> 00:42:49.300
DID I OFFEND YOU?
SORRY.

464
00:42:50.834 --> 00:42:54.004
YOU ARE
THE BASTARD THOUGH.

465
00:42:54.805 --> 00:42:57.641
LORD EDDARD STARK
IS MY FATHER.

466
00:42:58.342 --> 00:43:01.111
AND LADY STARK
IS NOT YOUR MOTHER.

467
00:43:01.111 --> 00:43:03.847
MAKING YOU THE BASTARD.

468
00:43:05.349 --> 00:43:08.852
LET ME GIVE YOU
SOME ADVICE. BASTARD.

469
00:43:09.720 --> 00:43:11.255
NEVER FORGET
WHAT YOU ARE.

470
00:43:11.255 --> 00:43:13.657
THE REST OF THE WORLD
WILL NOT.

471
00:43:13.657 --> 00:43:15.759
WEAR IT LIKE ARMOR

472
00:43:15.759 --> 00:43:18.996
AND IT CAN NEVER
BE USED TO HURT YOU.

473
00:43:19.930 --> 00:43:23.634
WHAT THE HELL
DO YOU KNOW ABOUT
BEING A BASTARD?

474
00:43:24.034 --> 00:43:28.339
ALL DWARVES ARE BASTARDS
IN THEIR FATHER'S EYES.

475
00:43:43.087 --> 00:43:46.256
( music playing.
chattering )

476
00:43:48.792 --> 00:43:53.931
YOU AT A FEAST--
IT'S LIKE A BEAR
IN A TRAP.

477
00:43:55.366 --> 00:43:57.635
THE BOY I BEHEADED--

478
00:43:57.635 --> 00:44:00.671
- DID YOU KNOW HIM?
- OF COURSE I DID.

479
00:44:00.671 --> 00:44:02.306
JUST A LAD.

480
00:44:02.306 --> 00:44:04.408
AND HE WAS TOUGH. NED.

481
00:44:04.408 --> 00:44:05.943
A TRUE RANGER.

482
00:44:05.943 --> 00:44:10.014
PFFT.
HE WAS TALKING MADNESS.

483
00:44:10.414 --> 00:44:12.716
SAID THE WALKERS
SLAUGHTERED HIS FRIENDS.

484
00:44:12.716 --> 00:44:15.986
THE TWO HE WAS WITH
ARE STILL MISSING.

485
00:44:17.187 --> 00:44:20.691
HMPH.
A WILDLING AMBUSH.

486
00:44:20.691 --> 00:44:21.992
MAYBE.

487
00:44:21.992 --> 00:44:25.696
DIREWOLVES
SOUTH OF THE WALL.

488
00:44:25.696 --> 00:44:27.731
TALK OF THE WALKERS.

489
00:44:27.731 --> 00:44:30.934
AND MY BROTHER MIGHT BE
THE NEXT HAND OF THE KING.

490
00:44:30.934 --> 00:44:34.371
WINTER IS COMING.

491
00:44:35.673 --> 00:44:37.708
WINTER IS COMING.

492
00:44:37.708 --> 00:44:38.942
( chuckles )

493
00:44:38.942 --> 00:44:41.945
- UNCLE BENJEN.
- ROBB BOY.

494
00:44:41.945 --> 00:44:43.814
- HOW ARE YOU?
- I'M GOOD.

495
00:44:43.814 --> 00:44:46.250
( laughter )

496
00:44:46.850 --> 00:44:49.420
IS THIS YOUR FIRST TIME
IN THE NORTH. YOUR GRACE?

497
00:44:49.420 --> 00:44:53.157
YES.
LOVELY COUNTRY.

498
00:44:56.026 --> 00:45:00.264
I'M SURE IT'S VERY GRIM
AFTER KING'S LANDING.

499
00:45:00.431 --> 00:45:03.100
I REMEMBER HOW SCARED I WAS
WHEN NED BROUGHT ME

500
00:45:03.100 --> 00:45:05.903
UP HERE
FOR THE FIRST TIME.

501
00:45:07.771 --> 00:45:09.907
HELLO. LITTLE DOVE.

502
00:45:10.474 --> 00:45:12.843
BUT YOU ARE A BEAUTY.

503
00:45:12.843 --> 00:45:14.845
- HOW OLD ARE YOU?
- 13. YOUR GRACE.

504
00:45:14.845 --> 00:45:17.781
YOU'RE TALL.
STILL GROWING?

505
00:45:17.781 --> 00:45:19.750
I THINK SO. YOUR GRACE.

506
00:45:19.750 --> 00:45:22.453
AND HAVE YOU BLED YET?

507
00:45:26.957 --> 00:45:29.026
NO. YOUR GRACE.

508
00:45:29.827 --> 00:45:32.730
YOUR DRESS.
DID YOU MAKE IT?

509
00:45:32.996 --> 00:45:37.201
SUCH A TALENT.
YOU MUST MAKE SOMETHING FOR ME.

510
00:45:38.135 --> 00:45:41.772
I HEAR WE MIGHT SHARE
A GRANDCHILD SOMEDAY.

511
00:45:41.772 --> 00:45:43.807
I HEAR THE SAME.

512
00:45:43.807 --> 00:45:45.743
YOUR DAUGHTER WILL
DO WELL IN THE CAPITAL.

513
00:45:45.743 --> 00:45:50.180
SUCH A BEAUTY
SHOULDN'T STAY HIDDEN
UP HERE FOREVER.

514
00:46:05.429 --> 00:46:09.166
- YOUR PARDON.
- I HEAR WE MIGHT BE
NEIGHBORS SOON.

515
00:46:09.166 --> 00:46:10.834
- I HOPE IT'S TRUE.
- YES.

516
00:46:10.834 --> 00:46:12.870
THE KING HAS HONORED ME
WITH HIS OFFER.

517
00:46:12.870 --> 00:46:14.138
I'M SURE WE'LL HAVE
A TOURNAMENT

518
00:46:14.138 --> 00:46:16.039
TO CELEBRATE
YOUR NEW TITLE--
IF YOU ACCEPT.

519
00:46:16.039 --> 00:46:18.308
IT WOULD BE GOOD
TO HAVE YOU ON THE FIELD.

520
00:46:18.308 --> 00:46:20.544
THE COMPETITION
HAS BECOME A BIT STALE.

521
00:46:20.544 --> 00:46:23.480
- I DON'T FIGHT
IN TOURNAMENTS.
- NO?

522
00:46:23.480 --> 00:46:24.515
GETTING
A LITTLE OLD FOR IT?

523
00:46:24.515 --> 00:46:28.452
( chuckles )
I DON'T FIGHT
IN TOURNAMENTS

524
00:46:28.452 --> 00:46:30.921
BECAUSE WHEN I FIGHT
A MAN FOR REAL

525
00:46:30.921 --> 00:46:33.857
I DON'T WANT HIM TO KNOW
WHAT I CAN DO.

526
00:46:35.459 --> 00:46:37.494
WELL SAID.

527
00:46:38.028 --> 00:46:41.131
- ( men laughing )
- ARYA!

528
00:46:41.131 --> 00:46:43.500
IT'S NOT FUNNY!

529
00:46:43.500 --> 00:46:46.236
SHE ALWAYS
DOES THIS.

530
00:46:46.236 --> 00:46:47.971
THIS WAS
MY FAVORITE DRESS.

531
00:46:47.971 --> 00:46:51.575
SHE ALWAYS DOES IT
AND IT'S NOT FUNNY!

532
00:46:51.575 --> 00:46:53.944
Robb:
TIME FOR BED.

533
00:46:55.145 --> 00:46:57.047
( groans )

534
00:47:04.521 --> 00:47:07.324
Ned:
I'M A NORTHMAN.

535
00:47:07.324 --> 00:47:09.560
I BELONG HERE WITH YOU.
NOT DOWN SOUTH

536
00:47:09.560 --> 00:47:12.963
IN THAT RATS' NEST
THEY CALL A CAPITAL.

537
00:47:13.497 --> 00:47:16.533
I WON'T LET HIM
TAKE YOU.

538
00:47:17.467 --> 00:47:20.103
THE KING
TAKES WHAT HE WANTS.

539
00:47:20.103 --> 00:47:23.307
( huffs )
THAT'S WHY HE'S KING.

540
00:47:24.208 --> 00:47:27.978
I'LL SAY.
"LISTEN. FAT MAN."

541
00:47:27.978 --> 00:47:28.846
( laughs )

542
00:47:28.846 --> 00:47:31.481
"YOU ARE NOT TAKING
MY HUSBAND ANYWHERE.

543
00:47:31.481 --> 00:47:34.318
HE BELONGS TO ME NOW."

544
00:47:37.588 --> 00:47:39.423
HOW DID HE GET SO FAT?

545
00:47:39.423 --> 00:47:43.126
HE ONLY STOPS EATING
WHEN IT'S TIME
FOR A DRINK.

546
00:47:44.294 --> 00:47:45.362
( knocks )

547
00:47:45.362 --> 00:47:48.565
Man:
IT'S MAESTER LUWIN.
MY LORD.

548
00:47:49.967 --> 00:47:52.469
SEND HIM IN.

549
00:47:54.004 --> 00:47:56.206
PARDON. MY LORD.
MY LADY.

550
00:47:56.206 --> 00:47:59.176
A RIDER IN THE NIGHT...

551
00:47:59.176 --> 00:48:01.511
FROM YOUR SISTER.

552
00:48:08.652 --> 00:48:11.555
- STAY.
- THIS WAS SENT
FROM THE EYRIE.

553
00:48:11.555 --> 00:48:14.424
( door closes )

554
00:48:17.361 --> 00:48:19.529
WHAT'S SHE DOING
AT THE EYRIE?

555
00:48:19.529 --> 00:48:23.000
SHE HASN'T BEEN BACK THERE
SINCE HER WEDDING.

556
00:48:31.241 --> 00:48:33.443
WHAT NEWS?

557
00:48:34.344 --> 00:48:37.347
SHE'S FLED
THE CAPITAL.

558
00:48:39.082 --> 00:48:42.019
SHE SAYS JON ARRYN
WAS MURDERED.

559
00:48:42.019 --> 00:48:43.553
BY THE LANNISTERS.

560
00:48:43.553 --> 00:48:46.556
SHE SAYS THE KING
IS IN DANGER.

561
00:48:46.556 --> 00:48:48.926
SHE'S FRESH WIDOWED. CAT.

562
00:48:48.926 --> 00:48:50.661
SHE DOESN'T KNOW
WHAT SHE'S SAYING.

563
00:48:50.661 --> 00:48:53.363
LYSA'S HEAD WOULD BE
ON A SPIKE RIGHT NOW

564
00:48:53.363 --> 00:48:55.632
IF THE WRONG PEOPLE
HAD FOUND THAT LETTER.

565
00:48:55.632 --> 00:48:58.535
DO YOU THINK SHE WOULD
RISK HER LIFE--

566
00:48:58.535 --> 00:48:59.670
HER SON'S LIFE--

567
00:48:59.670 --> 00:49:04.274
IF SHE WASN'T CERTAIN
HER HUSBAND WAS MURDERED?

568
00:49:11.014 --> 00:49:12.516
IF THIS NEWS IS TRUE

569
00:49:12.516 --> 00:49:15.953
AND THE LANNISTERS
CONSPIRE AGAINST
THE THRONE.

570
00:49:15.953 --> 00:49:19.189
WHO BUT YOU CAN
PROTECT THE KING?

571
00:49:19.189 --> 00:49:21.358
THEY MURDERED
THE LAST HAND.

572
00:49:21.358 --> 00:49:23.660
NOW YOU WANT NED
TO TAKE THE JOB?

573
00:49:23.660 --> 00:49:25.696
THE KING RODE
FOR A MONTH

574
00:49:25.696 --> 00:49:27.965
TO ASK FOR
LORD STARK'S HELP.

575
00:49:27.965 --> 00:49:30.734
HE'S THE ONLY ONE
HE TRUSTS.

576
00:49:31.735 --> 00:49:34.705
YOU SWORE THE KING
AN OATH. MY LORD.

577
00:49:34.705 --> 00:49:38.308
HE'S SPENT HALF HIS LIFE
FIGHTING ROBERT'S WARS.

578
00:49:38.308 --> 00:49:41.211
HE OWES HIM NOTHING.

579
00:49:42.312 --> 00:49:45.582
YOUR FATHER AND BROTHER
RODE SOUTH ONCE

580
00:49:45.582 --> 00:49:49.052
ON A KING'S DEMAND.

581
00:49:50.487 --> 00:49:53.090
A DIFFERENT TIME.

582
00:49:54.124 --> 00:49:56.560
A DIFFERENT KING.

583
00:49:59.363 --> 00:50:02.099
( drumming. clamoring )

584
00:50:22.753 --> 00:50:25.288
( hissing )

585
00:50:30.127 --> 00:50:32.496
( gasps )

586
00:50:48.712 --> 00:50:51.815
( jeering calls.
drumming continues )

587
00:50:56.720 --> 00:50:58.588
WHEN DO I MEET
WITH THE KHAL?

588
00:50:58.588 --> 00:51:00.457
WE NEED TO BEGIN
PLANNING THE INVASION.

589
00:51:00.457 --> 00:51:03.226
IF KHAL DROGO HAS
PROMISED YOU A CROWN.

590
00:51:03.226 --> 00:51:05.262
- YOU SHALL HAVE IT.
- WHEN?

591
00:51:05.262 --> 00:51:07.264
WHEN THEIR OMENS
FAVOR WAR.

592
00:51:07.264 --> 00:51:10.300
I PISS ON DOTHRAKI OMENS.

593
00:51:10.300 --> 00:51:14.304
I'VE WAITED 17 YEARS
TO GET MY THRONE BACK.

594
00:51:22.579 --> 00:51:26.483
- ( crowd ululating )
- ( grunting )

595
00:51:40.697 --> 00:51:43.467
( cheering )

596
00:51:51.641 --> 00:51:53.810
ETAYO AKKA.

597
00:51:53.810 --> 00:51:55.579
( blades clang )

598
00:52:04.721 --> 00:52:06.423
( screams )

599
00:52:13.697 --> 00:52:14.731
A DOTHRAKI WEDDING

600
00:52:14.731 --> 00:52:19.302
WITHOUT AT LEAST THREE DEATHS
IS CONSIDERED A DULL AFFAIR.

601
00:52:20.237 --> 00:52:22.672
( laughing )

602
00:52:31.248 --> 00:52:33.617
JADI.
ZHEY JORAH ANDAHLI!

603
00:52:33.617 --> 00:52:35.585
KHAL VEZHVEN.

604
00:52:40.657 --> 00:52:44.394
A SMALL GIFT.
FOR THE NEW KHALEESI--

605
00:52:44.794 --> 00:52:47.931
SONGS AND HISTORIES
FROM THE SEVEN KINGDOMS.

606
00:52:49.466 --> 00:52:51.234
THANK YOU. SER.

607
00:52:52.335 --> 00:52:54.771
ARE YOU FROM MY COUNTRY?

608
00:52:54.771 --> 00:52:56.940
SER JORAH MORMONT
OF BEAR ISLAND.

609
00:52:56.940 --> 00:52:59.609
I SERVED YOUR FATHER
FOR MANY YEARS.

610
00:52:59.609 --> 00:53:03.580
GODS BE GOOD. I HOPE TO ALWAYS
SERVE THE RIGHTFUL KING.

611
00:53:26.203 --> 00:53:28.572
Illyrio:
DRAGON'S EGGS. DAENERYS.

612
00:53:28.572 --> 00:53:31.575
FROM THE SHADOW LANDS
BEYOND ASSHAI.

613
00:53:31.575 --> 00:53:34.744
THE AGES HAVE
TURNED THEM TO STONE.

614
00:53:34.744 --> 00:53:37.514
BUT THEY WILL
ALWAYS BE BEAUTIFUL.

615
00:53:39.416 --> 00:54:46.549
THANK YOU. MAGISTER.

616
00:54:49.653 --> 00:54:52.455
SHE'S BEAUTIFUL.

617
00:54:55.692 --> 00:54:58.495
SER JORAH.
I DON'T KNOW HOW TO SAY

618
00:54:58.495 --> 00:54:59.829
THANK YOU
IN DOTHRAKI.

619
00:54:59.829 --> 00:55:03.600
THERE IS NO WORD
FOR THANK YOU IN DOTHRAKI.

620
00:55:24.387 --> 00:55:26.523
MAKE HIM HAPPY.

621
00:55:38.702 --> 00:55:41.604
( waves crashing )

622
00:56:25.815 --> 00:56:28.151
- NO.
- ( sobs )

623
00:56:30.820 --> 00:56:33.556
DO YOU KNOW
THE COMMON TONGUE?

624
00:56:37.494 --> 00:56:39.863
- ( pin clanks )
- NO.

625
00:56:43.032 --> 00:56:46.503
IS "NO" THE ONLY WORD
THAT YOU KNOW?

626
00:56:47.437 --> 00:56:49.139
NO.

627
00:56:54.411 --> 00:56:56.846
( sobbing continues )

628
00:57:17.100 --> 00:57:19.002
ROUGH NIGHT. IMP?

629
00:57:19.002 --> 00:57:21.004
IF I GET THROUGH THIS
WITHOUT SQUIRTING

630
00:57:21.004 --> 00:57:23.873
FROM ONE END OR THE OTHER
IT'LL BE A MIRACLE.

631
00:57:23.873 --> 00:57:25.809
I DIDN'T PICK YOU
FOR A HUNTER.

632
00:57:25.809 --> 00:57:29.779
THE GREATEST IN THE LAND--
MY SPEAR NEVER MISSES.

633
00:57:30.547 --> 00:57:33.583
IT'S NOT HUNTING
IF YOU PAY FOR IT.

634
00:57:41.024 --> 00:57:43.560
ARE YOU AS GOOD
WITH A SPEAR AS YOU
USED TO BE?

635
00:57:43.560 --> 00:57:46.529
NO. BUT I'M STILL
BETTER THAN YOU.

636
00:57:46.529 --> 00:57:48.665
( laughs )

637
00:57:48.932 --> 00:57:51.000
I KNOW WHAT I'M
PUTTING YOU THROUGH.

638
00:57:51.000 --> 00:57:53.703
THANK YOU FOR SAYING YES.

639
00:57:54.504 --> 00:57:57.574
I ONLY ASK YOU
BECAUSE I NEED YOU.

640
00:57:58.141 --> 00:57:59.976
YOU'RE A LOYAL FRIEND.

641
00:57:59.976 --> 00:58:03.680
YOU HEAR ME?
A LOYAL FRIEND.

642
00:58:03.680 --> 00:58:05.715
THE LAST ONE I'VE GOT.

643
00:58:06.783 --> 00:58:09.953
- I HOPE I'LL SERVE YOU WELL.
- YOU WILL.

644
00:58:09.953 --> 00:58:14.023
AND I'LL MAKE SURE YOU
DON'T LOOK SO FUCKING GRIM
ALL THE TIME.

645
00:58:14.757 --> 00:58:17.727
COME ON. BOYS.
LET'S GO KILL SOME BOAR!

646
00:58:27.537 --> 00:58:29.806
COME ON. YOU.

647
00:58:43.953 --> 00:58:46.589
( whines )

648
00:58:54.130 --> 00:58:56.065
( grunts )

649
00:58:59.736 --> 00:59:02.071
( soft barks )

650
00:59:07.977 --> 00:59:10.713
( woman gasping )

651
00:59:14.050 --> 00:59:16.986
( moaning )

652
00:59:25.862 --> 00:59:29.098
( grunting. moaning )

653
00:59:44.113 --> 00:59:46.616
( gasps )
STOP!

654
00:59:46.616 --> 00:59:48.918
- STOP.
- ( gasps )

655
00:59:52.722 --> 00:59:54.657
ARE YOU COMPLETELY MAD?

656
00:59:54.657 --> 00:59:57.860
- HE SAW US.
- IT'S ALL RIGHT.
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

657
00:59:57.860 --> 00:59:59.796
- IT'S ALL RIGHT.
- HE SAW US!

658
00:59:59.796 --> 01:00:02.599
I HEARD YOU
THE FIRST TIME.

659
01:00:03.299 --> 01:00:05.268
( whimpers )

660
01:00:05.835 --> 01:00:09.005
QUITE THE LITTLE CLIMBER.
AREN'T YOU?

661
01:00:09.739 --> 01:00:13.042
- HOW OLD ARE YOU. BOY?
- 10.

662
01:00:13.042 --> 01:00:14.877
10.

663
01:00:23.019 --> 01:00:25.989
THE THINGS
I DO FOR LOVE.

664
01:00:32.195 --> 01:00:35.331
( theme music playing )
